&lt;p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"&gt;"I never planned on going to graduate school, it wasn't something anyone in my family had done. But a professor saw something in me and encouraged me to apply. The first year was brutal. I struggled with imposter syndrome, fell behind on research, and almost dropped out. A mentor helped me find my footing and believe I belonged here. I defended my thesis last spring, and now I volunteer to mentor first-generation students going through the same thing."&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mattext>
